FBIS4-66027 "drweu103_e_94007" FBIS-WEU-94-103 Daily Report 25 May 1994 UNITED KINGDOM Government Announces New Order for RAF Missiles Government Announces New Order for RAF Missiles LD2505174594 London PRESS ASSOCIATION in English 1605 GMT 25 May 94 LD2505174594 London PRESS ASSOCIATION English BFN [By Parliamentary Staff, PRESS ASSOCIATION News] [Text] The Government tonight announced a fresh order for RAF [Royal Air Force] missiles awarded to British Aerospace. Defence Procurement Minister of State Jonathan Aitken said in a Commons written reply: "The contract for development and production of an initial batch of Advanced Short-Range Air-to-Air Missiles awarded to British Aerospace in March 1992 is proceeding well." He added: "Following a recent review of the operational requirements of the RAF's Harrier and new European Fighter aircraft, the contract for the follow-on order of a further quantity of missiles has been awarded to British Aerospace." Mr Aitken said the 66 million pound order was "excellent news" for British industry.
